This paper primarily focuses on Data Center Infrastructure Management (DCIM) and High Performance Computing (HPC), which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of Big Data technology, which is a subfield of Computer Engineering (cs.CE). The monitoring and analysis of environmental sensors and IT data points involve Network Infrastructure (cs.NI) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the optimization of operations and achieving greater efficiencies and reliability is related to Systems and Control (cs.SI).
